  {t:"Proverbs 27:23-24 — Know Your Numbers",v:"\"Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks, and look well to thy herds. For riches are not for ever: and doth the crown endure to every generation?\" — Proverbs 27:23-24 KJV",h:"In modern terms: check your bank balance, track your expenses, review your budget weekly. Know where you stand.",b:"Even if you're doing well right now, riches do not endure forever. One bad season, one unexpected expense can change everything. That's not a reason to fear. It's a reason to stay vigilant.\n\nApply it: Every Sunday, spend 10 minutes reviewing your budget and accounts. Make it a weekly habit like going to church."},
